IMPORTANT NOTICE REGARDING LV2 PLUGINS

Violet is an LV2 plugin host application. LV2 plugins are separate software
components that are NOT included with or part of this software. Each LV2
plugin has its own copyright holder(s) and license terms.

When using Violet with LV2 plugins:

1. PLUGINS ARE SEPARATE: LV2 plugins are independent software packages with
   their own authors, copyright holders, and license agreements.

2. PLUGIN LICENSES VARY: Plugins may be released under different licenses
   including but not limited to:
   - GPL (GNU General Public License) v2 or v3
   - LGPL (GNU Lesser General Public License)
   - MIT License
   - BSD License
   - Apache License
   - Proprietary/Commercial licenses
   - Other open source or closed source licenses

3. USER RESPONSIBILITY: It is the USER'S RESPONSIBILITY to:
   - Obtain plugins from legitimate sources
   - Review and comply with each plugin's license terms
   - Ensure they have the right to use each plugin
   - Respect plugin authors' copyright and licensing requirements

4. NO WARRANTY FOR PLUGINS: Violet developers make no warranties about
   third-party plugins and are not responsible for:
   - Plugin functionality, quality, or performance
   - Plugin compatibility or stability
   - Plugin licensing compliance
   - Any damages caused by third-party plugins

5. PLUGIN DISCOVERY: Violet scans for and loads LV2 plugins installed on
   your system. The presence of a plugin in Violet does not imply:
   - Endorsement by Violet developers
   - That the plugin is free or open source
   - Permission to use the plugin
   - Any warranty or support

6. COMMERCIAL USE: If you plan to use Violet with plugins in a commercial
   setting, ensure that:
   - You have proper licenses for all plugins used
   - Commercial use is permitted by each plugin's license
   - You comply with any additional terms for commercial usage

RECOMMENDED PLUGIN SOURCES

Free and Open Source LV2 Plugins:
- Guitarix (GPLv3): https://guitarix.org/
- Calf Studio Gear (LGPL): https://calf-studio-gear.org/
- LSP Plugins (LGPL): https://lsp-plug.in/
- ZamAudio (GPL): https://www.zamaudio.com/
- Invada Studio (GPL): https://launchpad.net/invada-studio
- MDA (MIT/GPL): http://mda.smartelectronix.com/

Always verify current license terms from the plugin authors.

